window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>National Book Critics Circle Award, Nonfiction, 2012</b></p> <p>After the American Revolution, 60,000 British loyalists fled the U.S. for Canada, the Caribbean, India, and other points abroad. Jasanoff traces their harrowing journeys across the globe, shedding light on their ambitions, the post-revolutionary world they encountered, and their legacies. </p>"; 
